trans-unit.source: Represents the desired size of the control's header, in pixels and in logical units.
This structure is used by the <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.Primitives.IHierarchicalVirtualizationAndScrollInfo"></xref> interface.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.HierarchicalVirtualizationHeaderDesiredSizes"></xref> class.
The size of the header, in logical units.
The size of the header, in [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_dipixel#plural](~/includes/tlasharptla-dipixelsharpplural-md.md)].
Returns a value that indicates whether the specified object is equal to this <xref href="System.Windows.Controls.HierarchicalVirtualizationHeaderDesiredSizes"></xref> object.
The object to compare.
`true` if the specified object is equal to this object; otherwise, `false`.
